article.description: Travis Fuller, Obi Okolie and Chris Sullivan scored 11 points apiece and Cedric Kuakumensah grabbed 18 rebounds as Brown beat Division III Daniel Webster College 69-43 on Saturday.
article.headline: Brown beats Division III Daniel Webster College 69-43
article.linkText: Brown beats Division III Daniel Webster College 69-43
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- Travis Fuller, Obi Okolie and Chris Sullivan scored 11 points apiece and Cedric Kuakumensah grabbed 18 rebounds as Brown beat Division III Daniel Webster College 69-43 on Saturday. The Bears (5-9) averaged 36.4 percent shooting from the field and 58.3 percent from the line. The bench contributed 44 of 69 points and the team finished with a 51-38 rebounding edge over Daniel Webster. After a 21-21 tie at the break, Brown used a 13-9 surge midway through the second half to take a 41-34 lead with 8:17 to play. JR Hobbie -- who finished with nine points -- sank a pair of 3-pointers after that to extend Brown's advantage to 46-36 with 6:22 remaining and the Bears cruised from there. Rondell Best led the Eagles with 12 points and 12 rebounds. Tevon Smallpiece added 10 points and seven rebounds.
